sentences: Mari Silje Samuelsen (born 21 December 1984) is a Norwegian violinist.
She earned two master's degrees at Zurich University of the Arts in Switzerland in 2012.
In 2014, Mari and HÃ¥kon performed the world premiere of Pas de Deux, a double concerto they commissioned James Horner to compose.
Samuelsen released her debut solo album, Mari, on 7 June 2019, via the label Deutsche Grammophon.
Her performance of Richter's composition "November" from Memoryhouse (2002) was released as a single before Mari was released.
For the last ten years, she has been a student of the world-renowned Russian professor and violinist Zakhar Bron.
She studied with Tellefsen in Oslo, and played with him for almost 10 years.
